<DOCNO> AP890522-0004 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the magellan spacecraft responded to a 
computer command and successfully corrected its trajectory sunday 
increasing the speed of its travel toward venus officials said 
the maneuver was completed at 7 pm sunday with a 56 second 
rocket burn said officials with the jet propulsion laboratory the 
lab controls the united states unmanned planetary explorations 
the correction increases the spacecrafts velocity by about 66 
miles per hour 
the spacecraft launched from the space shuttle atlantis on may 
4 hurtles at 60022 miles per hour as it continues its 15month 
journey toward venus there it will map most of the surface of the 
planet with imaging radar 
another maneuver to correct magellons path through space is set 
for aug 10 1990 17 days before the spacecraft enters orbit 
around venus 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

