wrongly gives county prosecutors complete and unguided discretion 
to determine whether to seek the death penalty in murder cases 
gacys appeal also had contended that he was denied a fair trial 
because the presiding judge limited the testimony of an expert 
psychiatric witness for the defense 
both arguments were rejected by the illinois supreme court last 
sept 29 
the high courts action came without comment other than a 
dissenting statement by justices william j brennan and thurgood 
marshall who oppose capital punishment under all circumstances 
