popular movements in the baltic republics are 
going too far in demanding greater independence and backing 
programs that amount to complete secession from the soviet union 
the communist party newspaper pravda said monday 
grassroots groups in estonia latvia and lithuania are issuing 
demands that are extremist and even nationalist the newspaper said 
referring to resolutions passed at a midmay assembly of baltic 
popular movements in estonia pravda said in total although no 
one talks about this directly they make sense only if their 
authors have in mind the complete secession of the three republics 
from the soviet union 
the baltic assembly stopped short of endorsing secession but 
many members of the estonian and latvian peoples fronts and the 
lithuanian movement sajudis openly espouse complete secession 
the pravda article came three days before the opening of a new 
national parliament at which at least one baltic delegation the 
lithuanians have threatened to walk out if their desires are 
ignored 
we think uzbeks or russians dont understand our problems 
said alfredas smailys a lithuanian delegate to the new congress of 
