<TEXT>
here at a glance are highlights of actions 
taken monday by the supreme court 
 
unification church 
 
the court refused to shield the rev sun myung moons 
unification church from being sued by two former members who say 
they were duped into joining it 
the court without comment rejected arguments that religious 
freedom protects the church against allegations of brainwashing 
and fraudulent recruiting 
the case is holy spirit association vs molko 881600 
 
john wayne gacy 
 
the court turned down an appeal by mass murderer john wayne 
gacy convicted and sentenced to death in 1980 for killing 33 boys 
and young men 
the justices rejected arguments that illinois death penalty law 
wrongly gives county prosecutors complete and unguided discretion 
to determine whether to seek the death penalty in murder cases 
gacys appeal also had contended that he was denied a fair trial 
because the presiding judge limited the testimony of an expert 
psychiatric witness for the defense 
the case is gacy vs illinois 886828 
 
evidence 
 
the court l limited federal judges power to exclude potentially 
prejudicial evidence from civil trials ruling against a young 
pennsylvania man who lost his arm in a car wash accident 
the justices by a 63 vote said paul greens productliability 
lawsuit was not denied a fair trial when lawyers representing the 
sued manufacturer were allowed to tell jurors about greens 
criminal record 
the case is green vs bock laundry machine co 871816 
 
social security 
 
the court agreed to study a federal regulation aimed at saving 
the government time and money when it mistakenly overpays some 
social security recipients 
the court said it will study a ruling in a colorado case that 
struck down the regulation 
the case is sullivan vs everhart 881323 
 
airport noise 
 
the court refused to shield chicago from being sued for monetary 
damages in state court for allegedly allowing excessive noise and 
air pollution at ohare international airport 
the justices without comment let stand a ruling that the court 
allow such lawsuits 
the cases are chicago vs beineman 881496 bieneman vs 
chicago 881497 and american airlines vs chicago 881670 
 
fraud 
 
the court rejected an appeal by a former chicago councilman 
convicted of fraud for illegally conspiring to buy and sell 
taxdelinquent properties 
the court over one dissenting vote refused to use the case of 
thomas e keane to set guidelines on when some people may challenge 
their fraud convictions after completing prison terms for those 
convictions 
the case is keane vs us 881178 
 
achille lauro 
 
the court ruled that a lawsuit stemming from the terrorist 
hijacking of the cruise ship achille lauro in 1985 may be tried in 
a federal court in new york city 
voting 90 the justices rejected an appeal by the ship owners 
aimed at transferring the suit to a court in naples italy 
the case is lauro lines vs chasser 8823 
 
prisoner 
 
the court made deadlines for the filing of civil rights lawsuits 
by some prison inmates more flexible 
the court unanimously ruled in a case from michigan that states 
may give prisoners extra leeway on when they file such federal 
suits 
the case is hardin vs straub 877023 
</TEXT>
