were bitter rivals at this stage of contract talks three years ago 
together our members are determined to win jobs with justice 
and a contract worthy of the skills and productivity of our 
members he said 
in 1986 cwa struck atampt for 26 days but the company was able to 
keep half of its manufacturing plants open because the ibew agreed 
to work provided its members were given any added benefits cwa won 
through its strike 
