<TEXT>
hundreds of house members boosted their income 
last year with speaking fees investments and money from such other 
sources as jewelry making and tv residuals disclosure forms showed 
monday house speaker jim wright paid off at least 105000 in debt 
but may have had to dig into personal assets to do it 
the most common addition to congressional pay was in fat fees 
from interest groups in exchange for giving speeches 
almost all house members have outside investments some 
substantial 
some earn money from previous careers including pensions 
some moonlight 
for example rep ben nighthorse campbell dcolo a northern 
cheyenne indian earned 5000 last year for his jewelry designs 
rep tom mcmillen dmd a former national basketball 
association player received deferred income totaling 45000 from 
the washington bullets and atlanta hawks he also reported 10000 
in income for renting space and equipment to his reelection 
campaign 
the disclosure forms filed annually by all 535 members of the 
house and senate provide a look at congress outside income and the 
wealth or lack thereof of each member each form lists a 
members money received his assets and liabilities 
the senate reports were released last friday 
house members are limited to earning an additional 30 percent 
or 26850 in honoraria for appearances most lawmakers donate 
anything over that to charity 
the forms do not provide precise data on congressional income 
listing only ranges for example properties worth 52000 and 
98000 respectively both would be listed in the 
50001to100000 range an asset worth millions could be listed 
simply as more than 250000 unless a member chose to spell it out 
this often shrouds the true wealth of an individual member but 
does provide a guide to where that lawmaker derives investment and 
other income 
wright who has been under investigation for allegations that he 
used his leadership position for financial gain got out of debt in 
1988 according to his disclosure statement 
his debt somewhere between 105000 and 200000 was paid off 
leaving wright with no financial liabilities 
his assets somewhere between 31005 to 100000 compared with 
a range of 155000 to 435000 in 1987 but the current accounting 
does not include holdings in the blind trust he established in 1987 
house members homes also neednt be listed 
the financial disclosure statements show that honoraria 
generally fees for outside speeches were an important part of the 
incomes of many of the 435 house members supplementing a federal 
salary which in most cases comes to 89500 
house majority whip tony coelho dcalif the thirdranking 
house democrat doubled his salary last year with 90100 from 53 
paid speeches to get under the house ceiling in honoraria he gave 
63575 to charity in 177 separate donations 
house republican leader bob michel of illinois reported income 
of 165865 to 180864 and assets of 165000 to 400000 he 
earned twice the 30000 wright earned in speaking fees giving 
30900 out of the total 60500 to charity 
michel listed some of the side benefits of taking part in 
charity golf tournaments 966 worth of golf clothing and 
paraphernalia from the bob hope desert classic the kemper open 
the jerry ford invitational and others 
