<TEXT>
a guerrilla facing execution for a 
1986 bombing that killed three people has married his girlfriend in 
an interracial wedding ceremony on death row a newspaper reported 
monday 
robert mcbride 25 of the african national congress was 
sentenced to death in april 1987 10 months after planting a bomb 
at a beachfront bar in durban that killed three women and injured 
69 people the blast came two days after president pw botha 
declared a national state of emergency 
the pretoria news said mcbride who is of mixed race married 
his white girlfriend paula in a ceremony conducted by an anglican 
minister at pretoria central prison on may 10 they decided not to 
publicize the marriage at the time and did not want the brides 
maiden name disclosed said the reporter who wrote the story 
the couple reportedly met almost daily over the past two years 
communicating through a glass window at the prison 
at his trial mcbride said he carried out the bombing on his own 
and feared punishment by the anc for violating its directives 
against hitting civilian targets the blast killed two whites and 
an indian most of the injured were white 
no execution date has been set mcbrides wife was quoted as 
saying she hoped the sentence would be commuted 
the justice department said monday that two black trade 
unionists on death row were reprieved by botha who commuted their 
sentences to 20year prison terms 
seven other prisoners are scheduled to be executed this week 
according to an organization of human rights lawyers 
