a crowd estimated at 200000 demanded at a rally 
in downtown yerevan that armenias president prime minister and 
communist party chief be replaced a local activist said monday 
rafael popoyan said in a telephone interview that the 
demonstration held sunday in the armenian capital also demanded 
resolution of the longfestering conflict over nagornokarabakh a 
largely armenian enclave in azerbaijan 
ethnic clashes over nagornokarabakh which many armenians want 
annexed to their southern republic killed more than 90 people last 
year 
popoyan said the rally decided to suspend a 4dayold general 
strike in anticipation of thursdays opening of the nations new 
parliament the congress of peoples deputies he said the strike 
may be renewed if the congress fails to address the question of 
nagornokarabakh 
