<TEXT>
the bush administration said monday it is 
studying a response from west germany to a proposed us compromise 
on the issue of shortrange missiles in europe 
deputy white house press secretary roman popadiuk said the 
response received monday afternoon had been discussed with 
president bush by national security adviser brent scowcroft 
popadiuk said he had no details or characterization of the 
latest proposal to cross the atlantic it is being studied he 
said 
however another us official speaking on condition of 
anonymity said the issue was still unsettled 
the official said the reply had neither advanced nor lessened 
prospects for a settlement were not home yet the official 
said 
bush on sunday voiced optimism that the uswest german dispute 
which has split nato would be resolved before the alliances 
40thanniversary meeting begins next monday in brussels 
the flap centers on whether to negotiate with the soviets on 
reducing the size of natos nuclear arsenal in western europe 
the west german government responding to heavy political 
pressure for disarmament has supported such talks the united 
states has generally held that eastwest negotiations on the 
weapons should begin until the easts superiority in conventional 
arms is erased 
last friday the us side gave west german defense minister 
gerhard stoltenberg a compromise offer that west german officials 
privately said opened the door to eventual ussoviet negotiations 
secretary of state james a baker iii who spent the weekend in 
kennebunkport maine with bush at the presidents oceanside 
retreat said saturday the german stance was too vague for a 
deal 
the germans thus far have insisted on leaving open the option of 
eliminating all nato and warsaw pact shortrange missiles in any 
negotiations 
under the us proposal meanwhile negotiations would be held 
only after nato and and warsaw pact nations agreed on cuts in 
conventional forces that would reduce the easts superiority 
earlier monday popadiuk called the issue a natowide issue 
and its one that affects all members and all members have a view 
on it and of course all views are welcome 
the issue will be worked and hopefully will be resolved before 
the nato summit so that we can have a successful nato summit 
popadiuk said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

