<TEXT>
the soviet union on monday suggested both nato and 
the warsaw pact be disbanded 
the warsaw treaty states propose disbanding both military 
alliances at the same time starting with disbanding of their 
military forces said foreign ministry spokesman gennady i 
gerasimov 
gerasimov said the full appeal to members of the north atlantic 
treaty organization would be published in soviet newspapers tuesday 
it is not the first time east european officials have broached 
the idea but mondays statement comes one week before a nato 
summit meeting that finds the 16nation western alliance divided 
over the depth of changes in the soviet threat 
west germany advocates talks on the elimination of shortrange 
nuclear weapons from europe while the united states and britain 
say no such talks are possible while the soviet union and its 
allies have overwhelming superiority 
a compromise reportedly is in the offing on the question of 
nuclear arms talks but fundamental differences remain within nato 
west germany is more concerned with eliminating the possibility of 
a destructive eastwest conflict on its territory since even a war 
that nato wins would likely be disastrous for germany 
president mikhail s gorbachev has offered the possibility of an 
undivided europe free of nuclear threat 
gerasimov said monday the east european alliance was suggesting 
expanding arms negotiations to all weapons systems including 
navies 
he said the appeal was being made because times have changed 
since the postwar era when the two alliances were formed 
east european officials have offered the hypothetical 
possibility of dissolving the warsaw pact once nato is disbanded 
and romanian leader nicolae ceausescu mentioned simultaneous 
dissolution years ago the topic has arisen recently in talks by 
hungarian officials contemplating neutrality 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

