time complains loudly that she wants to live with her daughter 
the photographer daughter played by anita gillette experiences 
guilt but realizes shed have to hire fulltime caretakers for her 
mother she patiently accepts her mothers abuse during weekly 
visits the daughters supportive lawyer roommatelover nan is 
played by kelly bishop who was the original brash sheila in a 
chorus line 
the playwright has the mother proclaiming aspects of her own 
personality some of them news to everybody else on stage more new 
personality traits for mom are written into the daughters 
throbbingly delivered eulogy while her mother is still alive 
this apparently is meant to show the mother as a complex person 
but it comes across as the writer throwing in everything she can 
think of and creating no person known to humanity 
three practical nurses often watch tv in the mothers room beth 
fowler plays an irish woman obsessed with the catholic church 
leila boyd a mothering black woman and olga merediz a sympathetic 
hispanic girl anne shropshire plays another old lady in the home 
vague but saintly 
the play of seemingly innumerable scenes is directed by roberta 
sklar 
