<TEXT>
these are the five main christian groups of the middle east 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
oriental orthodox churches founded in christianitys early 
years these are independent churches linked to specific nations or 
ethnic groups the coptic orthodox church believed founded by st 
mark in the year 50 is the largest in the middle east with about 7 
million followers mostly in egypt the others are the 2million 
member armenian orthodox church and the syrian orthodox church 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
eastern orthodox churches also known as greek orthodox these 
are selfgoverning and differ from the oriental orthodox churches 
on doctrinal decisions handed down before the year 800 the largest 
is the greek orthodox patriarch of antioch and all the east with 
about 13 million followers mostly in syria others include the 
the greek orthodox patriarchate of jerusalem the church of cyprus 
and the church of mount sinai represented by about a dozen monks 
at the famous shrine where moses is said to have received the ten 
commandments 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
catholics they consist of seven branches all but the maronite 
catholics the largest christian sect in lebanon broke from 
branches of the orthodox churches the maronites claim to have 1 
million members in lebanon and 67 million outside the region the 
others range in membership from 30000 to 300000 and include the 
chaldean catholic patriarchate of babylon the largest christian 
community in iraq and the syrian catholic patriarchate of antioch 
which celebrates its liturgy in jesus language of aramaic 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
assyrian church of the east its largest group 250000 
members is in baghdad iraq the church long been pilloried by 
others christians allegedly for following the teachings of 
nestorius an excommunicated 5th century patriarch of 
constantinople 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
protestants now numbering about 100000 members protestant 
churches were established in the middle east in the early 19th 
century by missionaries us evangelistic groups such as those 
led by the rev jerry falwell and the rev pat robertson are 
active in jerusalem and southern lebanon 
</TEXT>
