memories of me cbsfox home video vhsbeta 8998 rated 
pg13 
 
memories of me is almost a completely forgettable movie 
until its final third when theres finally some action to the 
drama about a father and son trying to reconcile their years of 
estrangement 
memories is henry winklers first outing as a director and 
it shows in the movies pacing much of the beginning is plodding 
and selfconsciously slow poignant moments when young dr abbie 
polin billy crystal reflects on his callous father hang 
relentlessly on dead air 
crystal cowrote the film and created a girlfriend jobeth 
williams for himself whose role in the melodramacomedy is vague 
at times her only purpose seems to be to admire crystals rear end 
or his sexual prowess 
the plot finally gets going when crystal after suffering a mild 
heart attack treks from new york to los angeles to resolve the 
decades of paternal indifference once hes there abbie learns his 
dad abe the king of hollywood extras alan king has a terminal 
illness 
they try to win abe a speaking part in a movie and validate his 
oftrepeated claim i am an actor in the process abbie comes 
to love his curmudgeonly dad who returns the favor by softening 
enough to tell abbie he loves him too and that in his role as 
father he was simply miscast 
it gets a bit cornball after this but the ending is far more 
compelling than the beginning and worth slogging through the slow 
start 
by patricia bibby associated press writer 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
motion picture association of america rating definitions 
g general audiences all ages admitted 
pg parental guidance suggested some material may not be 
suitable for children 
pg13 special parental guidance strongly suggested for 
children under 13 some material may be inappropriate for young 
children 
r restricted under 17 requires accompanying parent or adult 
guardian 
x no one under 17 admitted some states may have higher age 
restrictions 
